│ `%l` is uniform                                                             │
│ - `%gep.B = getelementptr inbounds float, ptr %B, i64 %iv` - this is        │
│ varying because it uses the induction variable                              │
│ - `%sel.ptr = select i1 %c, ptr %A, ptr %gep.B` - the condition `%c` is     │
│ uniform, but the operands are mixed (one uniform, one varying)              │
│                                                                             │
│ In vectorization, the select should be widened because one of its operands  │
│ is varying, even though the condition is uniform.                           │
│                                                                             │
│ The key insight from the root cause analysis is that during                 │
│ `replicateByVF`, we're processing a replicate recipe that is NOT single     │
│ scalar, but we want to replace users that only need the first lane with the │
